@@ -37,3 +37,31 @@ does a mob die in the same number of hits, take/deal the same damage, aggro from
 - **Damage formula form** = official NosTale = *hypothesis* for NosVoid; validate.
 - **Static tables** (if imported later) = inherited-baseline, NOT NosVoid-actual.
 - **Logged dynamics** (su/die/drop/move from your own play) = NosVoid-actual ground truth.
+
+## Phase 2 scaffold — Gymnasium env + scripted baseline (Session 21)
+
+`gym_env.py` wraps the simulator as a Gymnasium env; `scripted_baseline.py` is a
+greedy policy to beat. Soft dependency: both run even without gymnasium/numpy
+(install `gymnasium` to train with SB3/CleanRL/RLlib).
+
+```python
+from nosvoid_sim import FarmClearEnv, EnvConfig, evaluate
+evaluate(FarmClearEnv(), episodes=5)          # baseline clear-rate / time / deaths
+# python -m nosvoid_sim.scripted_baseline     # same, from the CLI
+```
+
+**Semi-MDP:** a `step` is one macro-action at a decision point, not a 100 ms tick:
+`0`=ATTACK (cast the AoE at the best reachable target, waiting out any remaining
+cooldown), `1..8`=MOVE one tile. Reward = `kill_bonus·kills − time_cost·Δt` with a
+terminal clear bonus / death penalty (so the return ≈ negative clear-time). The
+env auto-targets the densest reachable cluster on ATTACK; promote target choice to
+the action space later if needed.
+
+**Measured vs placeholder (important):** the PLAYER side is live-verified
+(targeted AoE r2 / range 9, CD 0.7 s, per-mob damage 101k/52k, crit ×2, HP ~306k,
+incoming 465). The MOB dynamics — `mob_step_ms`, `mob_attack_ms`, `leash_radius`,
+and `player_step_ms` — are PLACEHOLDERS in `EnvConfig`. There is also **no healing
+model** yet. So tiny clustered fights are faithful, but full-map *survival* /
+clear-time are NOT trustworthy until those three mob params are measured and a
+potion/lifesteal model is decided. Use this to wire training + as the baseline;
+gate RL on a measurable "RL minus script" clear-time win.
